pr_title: [GSOC 2022] Better DB model support based on old API
pr_body:
Because the output size of ppdetect(https://github.com/opencv/opencv_zoo/pull/66) is 1x1x-1x-1 but DB api is 1x-1x-1.I modify 'modules/dnn/src/model.cpp' as below.Still working on writing more tests
```
 //Support ppdetect
        int dim=binary.dims;
        if(dim==3){
            binary=binary.reshape(0,binary.size[1]);
        }

```
### Pull Request Readiness Checklist

See details at https://github.com/opencv/opencv/wiki/How_to_contribute#making-a-good-pull-request

- [x]  I agree to contribute to the project under Apache 2 License.
- [x]  To the best of my knowledge, the proposed patch is not based on a code under GPL or another license that is incompatible with OpenCV
- [x]  The PR is proposed to the proper branch
- [ ] There is a reference to the original bug report and related work
- [ ] There is accuracy test, performance test and test data in opencv_extra repository, if applicable
      Patch to opencv_extra has the same branch name.
- [x]  The feature is well documented and sample code can be built with the project CMake
pr_review_comments: [{'comment_id': 983415064, 'comment_body': 'I checked the models and it looks like the fix is reasonable. It makes sense to squash dimensions only if the extra dim has size 1. I propose to add `CV_assert` to raise issue, of some other model with unexpected output layout is used.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 9, 29, 11, 18, 40, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'asmorkalov', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 983531678, 'comment_body': 'I think we should edit the model graphs in [this](https://github.com/opencv/opencv_zoo/pull/66) PR, so that they have the right output shape, since in opencv model zoo models are tuned to work with OpenCV. This change is odd on its own.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 9, 29, 13, 17, 41, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'rogday', 'type': 'User'}]
